<div id="wrapper"><h2><a href="/output/Page2.asp"><img alt="" height="70" src="../files/images/XM_logo.gif" title="XM London Digital Communication" width="162" /></a></h2><h2><img width="190" alt="Case histories" height="80" border="0" src="/files/images/XM_L3_Clients_histories_shdr.gif" /></h2><p><strong>Foreign Commonwealth Office</strong></p><p>Having produced the original site in 1998, we were asked to create an updated version to take into account the increased usage of the web on a global basis and the opportunities this provides.</p><p>The site is designed to portray a more human face for the FCO whilst proactively demonstrating the online services the FCO offers (e.g. travel advice, speeches, forums, country profiles and a documents database).</p><p>Key to the planning and ultimate success of the site is information designed to create understanding and debate around complex policy issues within a templated structure that allows rapid response to global events.</p><p>The site uses an Open Market content management system to allow assets/information to be shared across a wide variety of other FCO sites.</p><p><a target="_blank" href="http://www.fco.gov.uk">http://www.fco.gov.uk</a></p><p> </p><p><img alt="Foreign Commonwealth Office website" border="0" height="195" src="/files/images/XM_L3_histories_fco_a.jpg" width="280" /></p><p><img alt="Foreign Commonwealth Office website" border="0" height="195" src="/files/images/XM_L3_histories_fco_b.jpg" width="280" /></p><img class="hide" src="/files/images/clear.gif" width="1" height="1" alt="" />
